{"id":473,"category_slug":"english-conversations","category_name":"Conversations","position":75,"title":"75. A Cashier","subtitle":"","level":"A2","parts":10,"url":"https://dailydictation.com/exercises/english-conversations/75-a-cashier.473/listen-and-type","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/english-conversations/75-a-cashier-2022-03-07-21-29-12/0-75-a-cashier.mp3","transcript":"What kind of work do you do?\nI'm a cashier at a supermarket.\nDo you like your job?\nNo, It's not very interesting.\nAnd you don't make much money.\nThat's right. I make very little.\nI think you should look for another job.\nI am, but it's not easy to find one.\nKeep looking! You'll get one.\nThanks. I hope you're right.","youtube_video_id":"","details_cached_at":"2026-06-15T20:49:00","challenges":[{"position":1,"content":"What kind of work do you do?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/english-conversations/75-a-cashier-2022-03-07-21-29-12/1.mp3","time_start":3.28,"time_end":4.84},{"position":2,"content":"I'm a cashier at a supermarket.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/english-conversations/75-a-cashier-2022-03-07-21-29-12/2.mp3","time_start":4.99,"time_end":6.84},{"position":3,"content":"Do you like your job?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/english-conversations/75-a-cashier-2022-03-07-21-29-12/3.mp3","time_start":6.84,"time_end":8.11},{"position":4,"content":"No, It's not very interesting.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/english-conversations/75-a-cashier-2022-03-07-21-29-12/4.mp3","time_start":8.14,"time_end":10.42},{"position":5,"content":"And you don't make much money.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/english-conversations/75-a-cashier-2022-03-07-21-29-12/5.mp3","time_start":10.48,"time_end":12.24},{"position":6,"content":"That's right. I make very little.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/english-conversations/75-a-cashier-2022-03-07-21-29-12/6.mp3","time_start":12.31,"time_end":14.23},{"position":7,"content":"I think you should look for another job.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/english-conversations/75-a-cashier-2022-03-07-21-29-12/7.mp3","time_start":14.33,"time_end":16.5},{"position":8,"content":"I am, but it's not easy to find one.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/english-conversations/75-a-cashier-2022-03-07-21-29-12/8.mp3","time_start":16.57,"time_end":18.93},{"position":9,"content":"Keep looking! You'll get one.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/english-conversations/75-a-cashier-2022-03-07-21-29-12/9.mp3","time_start":18.93,"time_end":20.78},{"position":10,"content":"Thanks. I hope you're right.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/english-conversations/75-a-cashier-2022-03-07-21-29-12/10.mp3","time_start":20.84,"time_end":22.67}]}